website_summaries.verdict: Great for someone looking for a versatile cart that can be used for more than drinks.
pros: Industrial, versatile design  makes this more than just a bar cart
Can be used for multiple indoor or outdoor purposes
cons: The look is more industrial and less stylish
Wire shelves can be unstable, and smaller objects can fall through

website_summaries.verdict: Customers looking for an all-purpose utility cart will find their match in this functional model.
pros: With weight evenly distributed, this cart can hold up to 500 pounds
cons: Some customers complained of the edges being a little sharp

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy Tool Cart
customer_reviews.text: I ordered this for my power tools, as I live in a small house and my garage isn't humidity controlled, so I have to keep my tools in my office closet. I loaded my giant miter saw on top, loose tools in the middle, and cases on the bottom. This cart handles the weight easily and is easy to push, even on carpet. It was easy to assemble and very sturdy. I'm going to buy another one for my hand tools and toolboxes. This makes wheeling out my power tools easy and makes me want to use them more often. So I'm running out of excuses.
customer_reviews.author: Dean C

customer_reviews.title: Oustanding Value
customer_reviews.text: Most of the bar carts I looked at were over priced, poorly constructed, and just plain ugly. This cart is an outstanding value, sturdy enough to house a full bar, and handsome in a formal setting.
customer_reviews.author: Bill38112

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy, but there's a trick to assemble
customer_reviews.text: I bought this cart as a stand for my sous-vide equipment in the kitchen. The top shelf gets my heavy chamber vacuum sealer and the lower shelves get the circulator and various canisters. The unit is very sturdy and the wheels are large diameter and work well. There is one issue to be aware or for assembly. The shelves have a specific right-side-up orientation to fit the locking sleeves on the upright rods. There is a "NSF" marking on corners of the shelves that must be right-side up or the shelves won't slide over the sleeves properly. As long as you pay attention to the orientation assembly will be easy.
customer_reviews.author: Rixter

customer_reviews.title: Perfect DM cart
customer_reviews.text: I use this cart to hold all my dungeon master materials for dungeons & dragons. It's perfect! I bought the hard plastic liners to go in it so my books and loose items are easy to manage. The three spacious shelves are enough for books, spell cards galore, lots of minis, map tiles, map mat, binders, laptop, and more. I have plenty of room to expand my collection and not feel crowded. Assembly was super quick and easy and the cart rolls fantastically. A+, would buy again.
customer_reviews.author: Lydia

customer_reviews.title: not good quality
customer_reviews.text: The metal pieces are very sturdy, but some of the plastic pieces were broken that were sent to put the thing together. I wound up using masking, duct, and packing tape to assemble the parts, I also used string to keep the shelves from slipping. I used metal bars so it did not collapse. It looked so bad when I finished that I put it out in the garage to use for storage. I would not recommend purchasing unless you are an innovative builder. I should have returned it, but once I opened the box, it would have been difficult to get everything back in, so decided to keep it.
customer_reviews.author: S.G.

customer_reviews.title: Be patient putting together this cart with the shelfs.
customer_reviews.text: The product is a good one but the instructions to put the cart together need to be improved. I had to figure it out for myself after many attempts. The plastic sleeves that are positioned to hold each level of the shelf is somewhat difficult. Making sure each level of the shelf is level is also not easy to assemble. There should be better markings on each of the horizontal bars to help make sure each shelf is level.
customer_reviews.author: tom raleigh

customer_reviews.title: commercial grade/no tools assembly required
customer_reviews.text: Very heavy duty Reminds me of the old metal wire shopping carts but looks better. Big heavy wheels. ABC instructions included. The last step top shelf takes a little force and good straight alignment to complete. You can adjust shelves and handle to desired height. Took me 20 minutes to complete and use it. Estimated arrival 1 week received it via amazon/UPS in 4 days. It looks so good thinking of using it occasionally as a porta-bar. The box it comes in I cut to size 2 liners for lower shelves and a piece of white poster board for my top shelf liner. maneuverability gave 4 stars because of blocked vision I run into things occasionally with the front wheels.
customer_reviews.author: jeffrey andersen

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy Cart with a lot of Room
customer_reviews.text: This cart is a great value. It was easy to assemble and is very sturdy. I ordered it because my employees stack a lot of items on their carts to take to classes they teach, and the plastic carts were falling apart because of the weight. This has held up perfectly and holds a lot of items. The shelves are spaced far enough in between that we can stack several items on top of each other on each shelf. This has been perfect for our needs and I would definately recommend to others looking for a sturdy, roomy cart that is affordable.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Using as a mobile work bench for a 12” compound miter saw
customer_reviews.text: I’m using this as a mobile workbench for my 12” compound miter saw. I had a 10” saw before and I could store it and move it easily. The larger saw had a significant enough weight difference that I needed something that I could use to store the saw in the garage but easily move it outside to the driveway when I need to use it. I placed the piece of plywood along the top of it and placed the saw on top of the plywood. I’m able to use the lower shelves to store other items. The plywood also helps keeps dust from falling to the items I’m storing on the lower shelves
customer_reviews.author: H

customer_reviews.title: Nice cart
customer_reviews.text: The material is good, but couldn't able to assemble the rolling cart because the plastic parts and the metal parts don't fit together. Have to return. Very disappointed. Update: I later found there are letters indicates how to put them together and I did it. So I changed the review from one star to four stars. I didn't give five star since I had hard time to assemble it.
customer_reviews.author: JD.W

customer_reviews.title: Attractive, well made  and usable for many different purposes.
customer_reviews.text: Attractive, well constructed cart at a nice weight. I liked it so well that I bought a second one! I use the first one for craft supplies for a Cardmaking group. My craft room is too small for our get togethers, so 8 transport them on this. Actually I have been leaving it in my dining room and using it there myself. The sevind is for in my pantry for my stand mixer and food processor plus attachments. I can wheel them into the kitchen when needed. Shoulder problems do not permit me to carry them and my kitchen is not suited to storing them there.
customer_reviews.author: stamper 82

customer_reviews.title: Solid quality and performance.
customer_reviews.text: Usually I am disappointed in items like this. They are usually poor quality and cheezy compared to the photos and description. Also usually missing components. This came well packaged, providing good protection from the rigors of shipping. It had quality well built components, extra hardware and great documentation. Easy to assemble. Greatly exceeded my expectations.
customer_reviews.author: Airboss

customer_reviews.title: Very Happy With this Cart
customer_reviews.text: The hardest part of this assembly was opening the VERY sturdy shipping box! In all, assembly took less than 30 minutes for one old woman working alone. Pieces are high quality (for the price), the wheels are sturdy with 2 locking wheels. Instructions were easy to follow. This one looks like a real keeper! Thank you Amazon.
customer_reviews.author: Kindle Customer

customer_reviews.title: Just buy them
customer_reviews.text: Nothing but good things to say about these units. I now have 4 of them. One is in the garage, one in the recreation room, and two in the family room. Good looking. Super heavy duty. Pretty easy to assemble. Just pay attention to the taper of the shelf sockets and the plastic bushings. Don’t bother buying less expensive ones. If you need sturdy ones, these are it.
customer_reviews.author: Jerry A

customer_reviews.title: Damaged connector
customer_reviews.text: I like the tray however one of the trays has a damaged connection cylinder so I was unable to use it. The cart is not a stable as it would be with the third tray attached but it will be ok. Returning such a heavy item would be difficult so I decided to keep it. It was very well packed so I think it was damaged before it was shipped.
customer_reviews.author: megb

customer_reviews.title: CAST IRON COOKWARE CART
customer_reviews.text: Showed up on time. The box and all parts were in perfect condition. I put this cart together in no time by myself. Everything fit together real tight and works perfect. I use it to move very heavy cast iron cookware on. And I plan on using it during canning season for those quart size mason glass jars. Thanks.
customer_reviews.author: LJC0867

customer_reviews.title: Super heavy-duty!
customer_reviews.text: Oh. my. goodness. I absolutely LOVE this cart! We recently moved into our new home which needs remodeling. We removed a wall between the dining room and kitchen so that we can make an island. But since we're doing all the work ourselves, we need to wait to complete it. In the meantime, I'm using a high top table and put this cart underneath with my kitchen aid mixer, Instapot, and other kitchen items. It actually looks kinda cool! The cart is super heavy-duty, so it'll have endless uses in numerous places in my home.
customer_reviews.author: Michelle

customer_reviews.title: Great product.
customer_reviews.text: Shipping was timely. Well worth the purchase price, in fact, would have paid more if necessary had I seen it in person instead of on the internet. Was east to assemble. Instructions simple to follow and understand. I am using this cart in my office for storge, supplies and four briefcases on the bottom self...if is PERFECT. It looks nice and not like some cheap cart one would purchase at the discount store. It is easy to move from one area to another and the wheels are very sturdy...moves well on carpet as well as wood or tile flooring. VERY PLEASED WITH THIS PURCHASE.
customer_reviews.author: Jerry Jasnoski

customer_reviews.title: Great quality storage solution. Need extra counter space for your Kitchenaid?
customer_reviews.text: I've been on a baking frenzy during quarantine. Both of my Kitchenaid mixers fit on top with room to spare. I roll the cart to the outlet, plug them in and use them on the cart. They cant "walk" while kneading dough. There's a lip to keep everything secure. I bought hooks to hang my accessories. All of my baking supplies, including my bin of flour, fit beautifully on this cart and I can simply roll it out of the way when finished. I spent a lot of time researching the best solution for my small kitchen/counter space and I couldn't be more happy! Professional grade. Seriously stable.
customer_reviews.author: Debra Loft

customer_reviews.title: Worth the money
customer_reviews.text: Great little cart. Making a top for it. Well worth the $$. However when we opened the box it was used. It had been assembled and taken apart and we know this because all the packing materials were broken and their was hair in the packaging ewwww. So 2 stars for sending me a used product.
customer_reviews.author: Genevieve LoBiondo

customer_reviews.title: Very very nice quality
customer_reviews.text: This cart is sooooo nice and quit beautiful to me. I needed it because i have 2 bad shoulders and can't carry my laundry baskets back and forth when the baskets are full. Also i wanted it for when i am decorating for holidays i will not have to go back and forth from where i store my stuff I'll just load it up and push my cart to where i need it. Im sure I'll find many uses for this beauty.
customer_reviews.author: C.w.C.♥

customer_reviews.title: Nice!
customer_reviews.text: Absolutely love this cart. We use it in our convenience store to put away groceries and stock. It moves really easy - up and over thresholds and hold quite a bit of weight. Priced very reasonable as well and NSF so we can use it in the kitchen as well.
customer_reviews.author: Loretta

customer_reviews.title: Heavy but great unit
customer_reviews.text: poles and support holes in the shelves are a bit larger than the other carts I own but plenty of extra hardware in case of accidents in assembly. Assembly is as simple as the others. Unit is quite heavy I can't think of anything heavy enough that this unit wouldn't support. Don't be afraid of the plastic sleeves that the shelves slide onto they act as "washers" once the shelves are in place. Any weight placed on the shelves only serves to make a tighter and stronger fit.
customer_reviews.author: c niezTop Contributor: Sewing

customer_reviews.title: sturdy cart but smells like oil
customer_reviews.text: The car is very sturdy. I think it would hold up for a lifetime. The chrome has a nice look. My only issue with it is the casters smell very strongly of the lubricating oil they use. After a week it still had not completely gone and i could still smell it in my kitchen. So unfortunately had to return it. I think if you're using it for a more industrial application it'll be great. just might not be best near your dining table. It's definitely better built than the cart i replaced it with the wires are heavier gauge and the chrome finish is nicer, but the new one doesn't smell like oil.
customer_reviews.author: RFS

customer_reviews.title: I keep buying these because they are GREAT
customer_reviews.text: I have over a dozen of these. I repair heavy electronics. Put a plywood cut to size and place it on top shelve. Put 11x14 photographic tray (remember these?), to place parts removed. I can easily move it away while I wait for parts. Efficiency booster. By the way, I do not use handles. It's much more maneuverable without it.
customer_reviews.author: tk

customer_reviews.title: Easy to put together and very sturdy cart.
customer_reviews.text: Great cart I've used one before at a place use to work at. The chrome plated coating is a drawback will oxidize over time. If there was a spray that could be applied to keep it from rusting? would be a great help? Very well constructed A+ !
customer_reviews.author: Marty

customer_reviews.title: I love it!
customer_reviews.text: Beautiful, quality product. Love the maneuverability with the handle. It is very attractive as well as sturdy. I use it to hold multiple bottles of mineral waters, sodas, juices for parties and guests and I leave those right in their boxes and set them on the cart. I can wheel it anywhere easily.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Is what they say it is
customer_reviews.text: As with every purchase, I perused the worst reviews first. They made me pause, but the percentages were in my favor, so I bought one of these. Thankfully, I got one of the 'perfect' packages and had no problems getting the unit together.
customer_reviews.author: Andrew

customer_reviews.title: VERSATILE!
customer_reviews.text: sturdy, moves easily, small criss cross pattern so small items don't fall through, adjustable. i use it in my office for end table. i also can keep the top shelf low enough for me because i am short, and like things lower. Most tables are too high for me.
customer_reviews.author: Jb h

customer_reviews.title: Awesome cart
customer_reviews.text: Love this cart! I use it in my kitchen for a convection oven that was taking up too much counter space. Was able to fit it in the middle shelf and put my coffee maker and accessories on the top shelf. Wheels on it move easy too.
customer_reviews.author: Cyn O

customer_reviews.title: Will put on a good show.
customer_reviews.text: Purchased to be used in a nightly show in Vegas. Has held up and going strong over at lease a hundred shows. It carries a lot of weight that you might not assume.
customer_reviews.author: Burly

customer_reviews.title: This is an amazing cart. Way better quality than I expected
customer_reviews.text: This is an amazing cart. Way better quality than I expected! It's so heavy, yet so easy to move around. I think three adults could sit on this thing with no problem. It is really heavy duty without being too bulky. A really professional look. I just love how it looks in the kitchen and it holds so much. The assembly couldn't have been easier, usually these kind of items are so frustrating to put together. It literally took 10 minutes and no tools. Snagged this as a lightening deal, so even better!
customer_reviews.author: babydollnut

customer_reviews.title: This is an excellent little cart for many purposes
customer_reviews.text: This is an excellent little cart for many purposes. I actually purchased two of them, because I needed a kitchen cart with more than three shelves to make the best use of my small kitchen space. (As far as I could tell, it wasn't possible to buy extra shelves for the first cart I bought; but if anyone knows otherwise, please let me know; because I now have the parts for a second cart, but with only one shelf ;-) It's very sturdy, and the wheels work well. We had no problem putting it together. Even if it were not so inexpensive, I would still think that it is a great cart; but the price is great, too.
customer_reviews.author: AMM

customer_reviews.title: Very impressed with the quality
customer_reviews.text: The cart was packaged well. There were several small plastic parts loose in the big box. They were not mentioned in the manual and were not needed for assembly. The assembly took approx 15 minutes. This cart is rock solid, no flexing or flimsiness, even when carrying weight. Well worth getting this IMO.
customer_reviews.author: Larry

customer_reviews.title: Durable and Dependable for Indoor Use
customer_reviews.text: The cart is durable and built to handle weight while still being stylish. I used it as a quick access & storage for my books and binders and many other items while working at home during this pandemic. Now that my work year is over, I am using it as a mobile craft station/storage. It is so easy to maneuver it around my room. I definitely know it is great to use it in an indoor setting. I want to get one for my garage or for storage outside my home and see if it handles just as good in an outdoor setting.
customer_reviews.author: N

customer_reviews.title: Great quality
customer_reviews.text: This rack is the perfect solution for all your small appliances. I have two Air fryers on top shelf and then a juicer, blender and food processor bases in 2nd shelf and accessories on 3rd shelf. I love it! Large enough to accommodate my needs but small enough to fit In the space. And the quality is amazing. Very sturdy.
customer_reviews.author: Tr2652

customer_reviews.title: Well designed, well made.
customer_reviews.text: In a field dominated by products that save a few cents by using chintzy materials and half-assed assembly methods, this product is a standout. It is heavily constructed and the manufacturing is first rate. Assembly is well thought out and simple, and the resulting cart is extremely sturdy. I couldn’t be more pleased. An added bonus is that the packaging is as good as the product, and protects the product during shipping without resorting to styrofoam.
customer_reviews.author: nancy robin morgan

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy
customer_reviews.text: I placed two of these in a closet nook under my stairs. They make storage items accessible. Love them!
customer_reviews.author: Polo Princess

customer_reviews.title: Very handy, easy to roll...
customer_reviews.text: I needed portable shelving for several of my small appliances...I wanted the countertops clear of clutter...perfect for what I needed, very sturdy, easy to roll, fits in an alcove where I have my washing machine...when I need to use something stored on it, I just roll it out, and it's right there...roll it back, everything is out of the way...
customer_reviews.author: peggys25

customer_reviews.title: Perfect answer for storage.
customer_reviews.text: We just down sized and needed extra storage. A cubbyhole off our kitchen is about 5’x3’x4h. This fit so well to hold less used appliances thatwe bought a second one for extra pantry storage. Their move ability makes them more useful.
customer_reviews.author: Cher

customer_reviews.title: Good...except arrived damaged...
customer_reviews.text: Took away one star because the product arrived damaged. The box looked fine, so it appears the damage occurred prior to boxing/shipping. One shelf "socket" was smashed enough to be out-of-round. We were able to insert a round bar into it and pound it into almost-round....and we used it as the top shelf (so it didn't have to travel as far down the leg). Aside from that, the product was easy to put together and as advertised....it is sturdy and works very well for the use we intended.
customer_reviews.author: Anne S.

customer_reviews.title: Love It
customer_reviews.text: This is a great cart with large, heavy, good quality wheels. There is a lot of space on each shelf and shelf heights are quite variable with the one inch increments on the poles. The shelves also have a small lip, so if items do move as you wheel the cart around, they don't fall off.
customer_reviews.author: Lori

customer_reviews.title: Great value.
customer_reviews.text: This was a very good decision for me because it fit the spot and the use I had in mind, and it arrived and performed as depicted online. The cross-hatch shelving is crucial because it supports even small items or soft items (like towels). The casters are quality. Recommended.
customer_reviews.author: CMcA

customer_reviews.title: Bought several
customer_reviews.text: I first bought this for work--several of them. Excellent utility cart. Can pull to right/left when load is not centered, but a minor point. Last one I bought to help my move to a new condo, then donated to my church and they love it as well.
customer_reviews.author: Beddie

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy, easy to put together, computer desk, etc. for my small retirement apartment.
customer_reviews.text: Moving into my small retirement apartment, I wanted a handy rolling desk - top shelf for my computer set up, second shelf for my meds, and bottom shelf has a cat cube sitting next to my printer. Love how easy SC carts are to put together and easy to move around for vacuuming, as well as nice space saver, and sure beats anything made of particle board. Will last the rest of my life. The handle bar is also great for hanging my leisure wear clothes.
customer_reviews.author: L. Ford Ballard, Jr.

customer_reviews.title: handsome and useful - my concern is it depends on paired plastic ...
customer_reviews.text: handsome and useful - my concern is it depends on paired plastic grips that snap together around the poles, using a less than 1 millimeter wide inner flange that fits in a similarly shallow groove in the pole (then you slide the shelf over them to put pressure squeezing the grip tight against the pole) to secure each of the adjustable shelves. Which means no way will I ever try to stand on the top shelf. But it has held up so far for piling on lots of heavy paper charts organized on racks that easily fit even under the top shelf
customer_reviews.author: Kindle Customer

customer_reviews.title: WELL DESIGNED STURDY CART VERY EASY TO ASSEMBLE
customer_reviews.text: I bought this as a way to mobilize my Snapple tea production with the 30 or so bottles I rewash and refill regularly. Last week though I wrenched my knee and ankle so now I am using it's sturdy build to serve as a walker and a transport for whatever I have to lug around from room to room. 500 lb capacity--I could even use it as a gurney for someone to push me around.
customer_reviews.author: JD

customer_reviews.title: Solid and sturdy chrome cart
customer_reviews.text: I am going to use the cart to store my strawberry, greens, and other container plants on over the winter. On warm, sunny, winter days I will easily be able to roll them outside into the sunshine.
customer_reviews.author: Cynthia Money

customer_reviews.title: Save time ... Make life easier ...
customer_reviews.text: No one ever said ... "I don't need help clearing the dinner table" ... This cart makes clearing the dinner table after a party... with only one trip to the kitchen ... possible and efficient ...
customer_reviews.author: Mark A Silverman

customer_reviews.title: Easy Assembly!
customer_reviews.text: This cart is so easy to assemble I couldn't believe my eyes! Sturdy and clean looking - I couldn't ask for a better cart. Will be using all over the office for deliveries. I love it so much i will probably buy more;)
customer_reviews.author: Matty88

customer_reviews.title: Love This Cart
customer_reviews.text: This is the perfect cart! It is beyond the sturdiest cart I've ever seen. I have it full of heavy plaster molds of various sizes that I make porcelain reproduction antique dolls with. The cart needs to be assembled, but with care it can be put together to be easy to roll and be easy to load and unload. Wish I would have gotten this cart sooner!
customer_reviews.author: ILDave

customer_reviews.title: Arrived damaged.
customer_reviews.text: Slight damage to corner of box. Plastic packing was shattered. Corner of one shelf not round so it did not fit over the slip sleeve. We assembled the shelf anyway to see if we could live with it, but it is not level and we expect more for a new item, so will have to disassemble and return. Would be nice if we could just get that one shelf replaced since everything else is good.
customer_reviews.author: Pat Empen

customer_reviews.title: Excellent cart for home dialysis use
customer_reviews.text: We needed a cart to hold a home peritoneal dialysis machine and various supplies. This cart works perfectly! Also, the cart is very sturdy and easy to assemble. The shelves can be set at different heights, too. An excellent cart for a very reasonable price!
customer_reviews.author: Sarah H

customer_reviews.title: Broken wheels. Replaced with wrong ones twice
customer_reviews.text: Cart was assembled and used for about 2 weeks. One of the wheels kept falling off causing so many spills... Manufacturer has sent me the wrong replacement wheels twice now. So cart has been useless for over a month and of course past return date. Trying to see what Amazon will do to help
customer_reviews.author: Falestine G.

customer_reviews.title: Description Accurate.
customer_reviews.text: This cart is sturdy, well priced and easy to assemble. The casters roll very well, even on commercial carpet tiles. I highly recommend this item.
customer_reviews.author: Elfcake

customer_reviews.title: Quality is better than expected for the price
customer_reviews.text: Wow, solid and very useful esp after surgery when one can't or shouldn't be lifting. Great for clearing a table or passing out food plates. All around useful cart and purchasing with reward points made it almost free!
customer_reviews.author: GatorRay

customer_reviews.title: Awesome buy!
customer_reviews.text: Great cart! I use this for my 10 gallon electric brew in bag system. It holds all my hoses, plate chiller hop spider, controller, etc... I brew right on the cart and the wire shelf dissipates the heat, so it never gets hot. (Small correction: 5 gallon system with 10.5 gallon capacity kettle)
customer_reviews.author: Cliff Roberts

customer_reviews.title: Very heavy duty, easy to assemble
customer_reviews.text: I was worried when the box arrived destroyed, however the real box inside was very heavy duty and totally intact, there were some destroyed plastic parts in the box, I quickly determined that these were shipping spacers and were disposable. The cart itself is very heavy duty, easy to assemble, the casters seem heavy and large enough, the finish seems nice I don't see any areas where it is thinner at the welds etc, which is common with other products. The spacing of the shelves is fully adjustable as you see fit. Aside from it being made in China, I'm very happy.
customer_reviews.author: moosel

customer_reviews.title: Love this cart!!
customer_reviews.text: Love this cart. Rugged, heavy duty. Very sturdy. I was a little concerned about the assembly due to some of the previous comments, but I had no problem. Assembled it by myself in about 15 minutes. I chose not to install the handle so it is a couple inches smaller. The handle really isn't needed. I will probably buy another one in the near future.
customer_reviews.author: Bucketcats

customer_reviews.title: Very nice cart. Difficult to assemble.
customer_reviews.text: The cart is very nice for the price. Maneuvers easily. The only thing I found very difficult was the assembly. The slip sleeves kept falling apart when I was trying to put the shelves on. After assembly I really like the cart. Casters are sturdy as well.
customer_reviews.author: Lisa Feil

customer_reviews.title: Not a bad cart
customer_reviews.text: Not as good of quality as the last one I received. I can't deduct any stars because it was my own fault for ordering the wrong one. This cart is lighter and doesn't push pull as well. Still will get the job done but spend the extra money and get the one listed below. Spend the extra money and get this one
customer_reviews.author: Jill

customer_reviews.title: Well Built Heavy duty Cart.
customer_reviews.text: This is an excellent cart. We purchased the cart to move our small kitchen appliances from the storage / pantry to the kitchen. Has worked perfectly for our needs. Very well built and was easy to assemble the instructions were very clear. My wife wonders how we ever got along without this cart.
customer_reviews.author: Jerry Walls

customer_reviews.title: Surface length NOT 34"
customer_reviews.text: I was quite disappointed with the size. Apparently 34" long, included the handle. The surface is not quite 30" long. It appears quite sturdy though.
customer_reviews.author: Hawaii shopper

customer_reviews.title: Cart is very nice, heavy and a good cart
customer_reviews.text: Cart is very nice, heavy and a good cart. The problem is the wheels. They go every which way and you can't change the direction when they move. Sometimes the wheels are turned backward and moving forward. either needs heaver wheels or some kind of mechanism to make them go the direction you want them to go.
customer_reviews.author: Joan M., Bell

customer_reviews.title: A very sturdy built cart for a small cart
customer_reviews.text: It was just as described. It is heavy duty for a small cart and perfect for what I needed. I rolled some things out to my car and now one of the wheels is wonky so I couldn't give a full 5 stars. However, still worth the price.
customer_reviews.author: Chef Mom

customer_reviews.title: Exceeded my expectations!
customer_reviews.text: I got this to store various small kitchen appliances so I can roll it out and easily use things like the quesadilla maker, Belgian waffle maker or indoor grill, etc. and then roll back to the pantry. Very easy to assemble and I am amazed at how sturdy it is! It is commercial kitchen quality! I will be buying more of these!
customer_reviews.author: Elaine J. Sutherland

customer_reviews.title: Stylish and durable
customer_reviews.text: I have both my Ninja Food and Kitchen Aid mixer on the top shelf and they have plenty of room. The entire cart is strong and sturdy. I wasn't sure about it with such a reasonable price point but it exceeds my expectations.

customer_reviews.title: Even though highly rated, I GOT A CRAP ONE - SAVE YOUR MONEY! BUY SOMETHING ELSE!!!!

product_meta.title: Seville Classics 3-Tier UltraDurable Commercial-Grade NSF-Certifed Storage Utility Service Cart, 34" W, Chrome
product_meta.description:
Size:34" W| Color:Chrome

Transport your things quickly and easily with Seville Classic’s 3-Tier Commercial Utility Cart. Choose the right cart for you home, kitchen, stockroom, or warehouse. Cart includes three tiers of storage, each height-adjustable at 1-inch increments. A large rounded steel handle provides easy control when empty or full. The unit consturucted of industrial-strength steel and protected with UltraZinc plating for defense against corrossion in dry environments. Designed for professional use, the cart is NSF certified for use in dry environments. It has a weight limit of 500 lbs. evenly distributed between shleves. Includes four swivel wheels, 2 locking. Cart measures 34 inches wide by 18 inches deep and 33.5 inches high when fully assembled. No tools required for assembly.



 * UltraZinc plating provides necessary corrosion resistance in dry environments
 * Handle bar allows for easy while maneuvering 
 * Industrial-strength steel wire construction for multipurpose use
 * NSF certified for commercial, residential and office spaces
 * Each shelf holds up to 150 lbs. in systems on leveling feet 
 * Wheels (4-inch diameter) allow for easy positioning 
 * Shelves are height adjustable by 1-inch increments; no tools required
 * Limited 10-year warranty



Specifications
Dimensions: 18"" D x 34"" W x 33.5"" H
Dimensions (w/o handle bar & wheels): 18"" D x 30"" W x 32"" H
Weight Capacity: 500 lbs. 
Weight: 42 lbs.
Model #: SHE18304BZ

Limited 10-Year Warranty
Seville Classics shelving is backed by a 10-year limited warranty unless otherwise specified. The warranty protects against original defects in material or workmanship under normal home or office use for the duration of the warranty period.
